                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bogota</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-03-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Colombian minister at Washington has already telegraphed ratification by the
                    Senate of the United States. Opposition developing. The enemies (?) of the
                    President attacking the assembly, demanding elected Congress and the amendment
                    Jurado (?) clause. Ratification is certain unless Reyes weakens. Final vote, it
                    is hoped, by Friday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
